doctype html(lang='en')
head
  meta(charset='utf-8')
  meta(http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible', content='IE=edge')
  meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1')
  // The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags
  base(href='/')
  meta(name='description', content='')
  meta(name='author', content='')
  link(rel='icon', href='favicon.ico')
  title Samurai Sales Interview
  // Bootstrap core CSS
  link(href='bower_components/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css', rel='stylesheet')

  link(href='bower_components/angular-motion/dist/angular-motion.min.css', rel='stylesheet')

  // Custom styles for this template
  link(href='css/style.css', rel='stylesheet')

  // HTML5 shim and Respond.js for IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries
  //if lt IE 9
    script(src='https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js')
    |
    script(src='https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js')
body(ng-app='interviewApp' ng-controller='interviewCtrl' style='background:#34495e; color: white; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 20px;')
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-6
        center
          h1 Samurai Sales Interview
          p Hi, thank you for your interest in Samurai Sales. Just to recap, this is a telesales position where all the work is done from your browser. We have built an online calling tool that allows you to work from anywhere as a telesales agent. The types of calling campaigns you can work on will vary from client to client.
          p The purpose of this interview is for us to get a sense of how you sound on the phone. All of this will be recorded, so we can review it at a later date. We have recorded ourselves asking some questions. Once you start the interview, a "Play question" button will appear to the right. You'll usually spend 1-3 minutes answering each question. Once you've answer this question, you can move to the next question by pressing the "Play question" button again. Once there are no more questions, press "End interview" to finish the interview. You can finish the interview at any time.
          p After the interview, we will get back to you within a few days to tell you how it went. Best of luck!
          button.btn.btn-lg.btn-success(ng-click='startInterview()' ng-show='index == -1') Start interview
      .col-md-6(ng-repeat='audio in audios')
        h3(ng-show='show($index)') Question {{$index+1}}
        button.btn.btn-lg.btn-danger(ng-click='endInterview()' ng-show='showEnd()') End interview
        a.btn.btn-primary(onclick="this.firstChild.play()" ng-click='increment()' ng-show='show($index)')
          audio(ng-src="{{audio}}")
          | Play question

        p {{question[$index]}}
  // /container

  script(src='bower_components/jquery/dist/jquery.min.js')
  script(src='bower_components/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.min.js')
  script(src='bower_components/angular/angular.min.js')
  script(src='bower_components/angular-sanitize/angular-sanitize.min.js')
  script(src='bower_components/angular-animate/angular-animate.min.js')
  script(src='bower_components/angular-strap/dist/angular-strap.min.js')
  script(src='bower_components/angular-strap/dist/angular-strap.tpl.min.js')
  script(src='//static.twilio.com/libs/twiliojs/1.2/twilio.min.js')
  script(src='js/interview.js')